Practical: 5.1 (activity, main setSupportActionBar(toolbar);)
Problem Statement Design and develop an Android application that displays an AppBar (Toolbar) at the top of the screen. The AppBar should show the application title and remain 
visible across the application interface to provide a consistent user experience. The title of the AppBar should be updated dynamically at runtime.
Project Configuration
      Project Name: DynamicAppBarDemo

activity_main.xml
            <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
            <androidx.coordinatorlayout.widget.CoordinatorLayout
                xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
                xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent">
                <!-- AppBar -->
                <com.google.android.material.appbar.MaterialToolbar
                    android:id="@+id/toolbar"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
